parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and hesitation can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, and may leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or lurches forward when accelerating
the vehicle slows down and comes to a standstill
the vehicle fails to start after stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel injectors can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: thick white smoke comes out of the back of the vehicle
the vehicle fails to start or restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause a distraction, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, and potentially causing injuries from flying glass shards.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes or shatters without warning
glass shards fall into the cabin
similar to a bomb going off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Fuel Sending Unit and Fuel Gauge
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel sending unit and fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel without warning, leading to a sudden loss of power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on busy highways or roads with no shoulder.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is stuck or inaccurate
the vehicle runs out of fuel without warning
the vehicle loses power while driving
the vehicle is unable to restart
the fuel gauge reports an incorrect fuel level.
